news.title: Gurugram development body directs M3M Woodshire to fix unauthorised connections
news.para: During an inspection by GMDA officials, it was found that 450 kilolitres per day (KLD) of water were being drawn through the pipeline, and only 150 KLD reached the condominium.

news.title: E-khata issues to be sorted out in 10 days: Bengaluru civic body
news.para: Thousands of applications are being submitted daily, but persistent delays have left residents frustrated.

news.title: CA Technologies’ India arm renews lease for 1.08 lakh sq ft office in Pune’s Kharadi
news.para: The software solutions provider for managing information technology infrastructure and services will be paying rentals of Rs 1.08 crore per month initially.

news.title: Nearly 47% of PMAY-Urban houses remain unoccupied due to lack of infrastructure
news.para: The parliamentary panel on the housing and urban affairs ministry has stated that the failure to occupy these houses, for “whatsoever reason”, will defeat the very purpose of the mission.

news.title: Shriram Finance sells entire stake in housing finance arm to Warburg Pincus for Rs 3,929 crore
news.para: The company had sold its over 84 per cent stake to the private equity fund for a consideration of Rs 3,929 crore a few months ago, a statement said.

news.title: Gauri Khan gets approval from MCZMA to add two floors to Bandra home
news.para: A presentation on the construction of the additional two floors was made before the Maharashtra Coastal Zone Management Authority (MCZMA), and a structural stability certificate was submitted for the existing building.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespace gets tax demand of Rs 2.09 crore from GST department in Tamil Nadu
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Mahindra Lifespace Developers Ltd said the "company has received order from the Office of the Assistant Commissioner of State Tax, Chengalpattu, Assessment Circle Tamil Nadu, GST imposing tax demand along with interest and penalty."

news.title: AAI seeks pre-feasibility reports for construction of Bhagalpur airport
news.para: The choice of deputy CM-cum-finance minister, Samrat Chowdhary, for the new airport has been Sultanganj. He is of the view that Sultanganj is strategically located and has connectivity with several districts.

news.title: Landmark's London office tower sale falls through on pricing deadlock
news.para: A deal at that level would have represented one of the largest transactions in European real estate this year, but the two parties failed to agree on a price for the building at 70 St Mary's Axe, locally known as the 'Can of Ham'.

news.title: HUDCO to provide consultancy to DDA for residential, commercial and institutional projects
news.para: In a regulatory filing on Wednesday, HUDCO said it has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with Delhi Development Authority, a statutory body established under the Delhi Development Act, 1957.

news.title: Migsun Group invests Rs 160 crore in a mixed-use project in Greater Noida
news.para: The project features a blend of retail shops, a food court, and premium business suites.

news.title: Thailand's cabinet approves measures to ease household debt
news.para: The measures will support retail borrowers and smaller businesses and solve debt problems in a more tangible and sustainable way, she told a press conference.

news.title: Shubham housing development finance raises Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: Existing investors Asian Development Bank (ADB) and British International Investment (BII) also participated in the round, which consists of a mix of primary and secondary transactions.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to demolish dilapidated building in Madan Paul Lane
news.para: Large parts of the façade of the building collapsed on Saturday night, prompting the CM to conduct an survey of the century-old building. She instructed KMC to arrange for a temporary shelter for the tenants and demolish the building to prevent any untoward events.

news.title: Govt to build metro corridor connecting India Gate, North, South blocks to Indraprastha station
news.para: The Delhi Metro Rail Corporation (DMRC) has been asked to finalise the proposed alignment, they said, adding it will be an extension of the Inderlok-Indraprastha metro corridor that was approved by the Union Cabinet earlier this year.

news.title: RITES prepares two route plans for Bhagalpur metro rail project
news.para: Detailed groundwork, including the comprehensive mobility plan (CMP), alternative analysis report (AAR) and a detailed project report (DPR), has been initiated to assess the feasibility of this ambitious project.

news.title: Delhi HC orders DDA to cooperate with CBI in Signature View apartments probe
news.para: In a recent order, Justice Chandra Dhari Singh factored in the submission of CBI that despite reminders, DDA has not yet informed it if any internal inquiry was conducted to fix responsibility nor has it furnished the names of officials involved so that the investigating agency can proceed with its criminal probe.

news.title: UltraTech leads cement stocks rally with 2.7% rise on price hike
news.para: The price hikes, which signal a recovery in demand, sparked gains across the sector, with Adani Group’s ACC and Ambuja Cements up 2% and 1.8%, respectively, and Dalmia Bharat climbing 3.4%.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: CRDA approves Rs 8,822 crore worth of projects in Amaravati
news.para: While talking to the media on Tuesday, Andhra Pradesh Municipal Administration and Urban Development Minister P Narayana said that Rs 3,807 crore has been allotted for the construction of roads in the areas in which land is acquired under the land pooling scheme.

news.title: Kolkata: Two housing communities leading way in green practices
news.para: Though starkly different in size and setting, their commitment to eco-friendly practices and climate-conscious living unites them in the battle against pollution and environmental degradation.
